sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant KRP as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS 1.2+
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Upstream as Upstream Application<br/>8081/TCP HTTP<br/>(localhost)

    Note over Client,Upstream: Flow 1: Authenticated Request Proxying

    Client->>KRP: HTTPS Request<br/>Port: 8443/TCP<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / OIDC JWT / X.509 cert<br/>Encryption: TLS 1.2+

    Note over KRP: Step 1: TLS termination

    Note over KRP: Step 2: Authentication<br/>(WithAuthentication filter)

    alt Bearer Token Authentication
        KRP->>K8sAPI: POST /apis/authentication.k8s.io/v1/tokenreviews<br/>Port: 443/TCP<br/>Auth: Service Account Token<br/>Encryption: TLS 1.2+
        K8sAPI-->>KRP: TokenReview Response<br/>(authenticated: true/false, user info)
    else OIDC JWT Authentication
        Note over KRP: Validate JWT locally<br/>against cached JWKS<br/>(fetched from OIDC issuer)
    else X.509 Client Certificate
        Note over KRP: Validate client cert<br/>against configured CA
    end

    Note over KRP: Step 3: Authorization<br/>(WithAuthorization filter)

    alt Hardcoded Metrics Path
        Note over KRP: prometheus-k8s SA + GET /metrics<br/>→ Hardcoded ALLOW (no API call)
    else Static Authorization Rules
        Note over KRP: Check static rules<br/>(if configured)
    else SubjectAccessReview
        KRP->>K8sAPI: POST /apis/authorization.k8s.io/v1/subjectaccessreviews<br/>Port: 443/TCP<br/>Auth: Service Account Token<br/>Encryption: TLS 1.2+<br/>(Format1: resourceAttributes + rewrites<br/> or Format2: endpoint rules)
        K8sAPI-->>KRP: SubjectAccessReview Response<br/>(allowed: true/false)
    end

    Note over KRP: Step 4: Set auth headers<br/>(WithAuthHeaders filter)<br/>X-Remote-User, X-Remote-Groups

    KRP->>Upstream: HTTP Request<br/>Port: 8081/TCP<br/>Auth: None (or mTLS)<br/>Encryption: Plaintext (localhost)<br/>Headers: X-Remote-User, X-Remote-Groups

    Upstream-->>KRP: HTTP Response

    KRP-->>Client: HTTPS Response<br/>Port: 8443/TCP<br/>Encryption: TLS 1.2+

    Note over Client,Upstream: Flow 2: Prometheus Metrics Scraping

    participant Prom as prometheus-k8s SA<br/>(openshift-monitoring)

    Prom->>KRP: GET /metrics<br/>Port: 8443/TCP<br/>Auth: SA Bearer Token<br/>Encryption: TLS 1.2+

    Note over KRP: TokenReview authenticates SA

    KRP->>K8sAPI: POST TokenReview<br/>Port: 443/TCP

    K8sAPI-->>KRP: Authenticated as<br/>system:serviceaccount:<br/>openshift-monitoring:prometheus-k8s

    Note over KRP: Hardcoded Authorizer:<br/>ALLOW (fast-path,<br/>no SAR needed)

    KRP->>Upstream: GET /metrics<br/>Port: 8081/TCP<br/>Plaintext (localhost)

    Upstream-->>KRP: Metrics Response<br/>(Prometheus format)

    KRP-->>Prom: HTTPS Response<br/>Port: 8443/TCP<br/>TLS 1.2+
